
// The code uses [set-value] to modify the value of a node referenced by [.json]. It first splits a string into multiple parts using [strings.split], and then joins these parts back together with a colon (":") as a separator using [strings.join]. The final result is assigned to the [.json] node.
set-value:x:@.json
   strings.join:x:@strings.split/*
      .:":"
